# Git Ignore Configuration
# Specifies intentionally untracked files that Git should ignore

# ───────────────────────────────────────────
# CRITICAL: Override global gitignore
# ───────────────────────────────────────────
# The global ~/.gitignore_global ignores /.opencode/ for symlinked repos.
# But THIS repo is the SOURCE of .opencode/ content - it MUST be tracked.
# The negation pattern below overrides the global ignore.
!.opencode/
!specs

# ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Archive
# ───────────────────────────────────────────
.opencode/agents/.provider-backups/
.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/_sandbox/*/fixtures/states/*.tar.gz

# ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Eval-rig runtime materialization (repo-root only)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────
# The 113/120 eval-rig fixtures use a relative `scope.cwd: fixtures/fix-NNN/seed`.
# Running the rig with the repo root as cwd (instead of RIG_ROOT) materializes a
# stray /fixtures/ tree here. The canonical fixtures + seeds live under each
# packet's eval-rig/fixtures/. Root-anchored so .opencode/**/fixtures/ is unaffected.
/fixtures/

# ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Build output
# ───────────────────────────────────────────
build/
dist/
.opencode/output/

# Generated lane-weight-sweep diagnostic reports (test artifacts)
sweep-reports/

# ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Certificates & secrets
# ───────────────────────────────────────────
*.cert
*.key
*.pem

